# DMVSOS — DMV Test Prep Platform

## Project Overview
Web platform helping immigrants pass DMV/DOL knowledge exams in the US.
Site: dmvsos.com

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- Tailwind CSS
- Supabase (database + auth)
- Vercel (hosting)

## Core Principles
- Immigrant-first UX: simple language, short sentences, clear explanations
- Government-source accuracy: questions based strictly on official state manuals
- Multi-state: WA, CA, NY, TX, FL and more
- Multi-language: EN, RU, ES, ZH, UK
- Two auth modes: Guest (no signup) + OAuth (Google, Apple)

## Pages We Are Building
1. Home page — state selector, category picker
2. Test screen — question, 4 options, progress bar, timer
3. Result screen — score, error review
4. Dashboard — user history, weak topics

## Database (Supabase)
- questions: id, state, category, language, question_text, option_a/b/c/d, correct_answer, explanation, manual_version
- test_sessions: id, user_id, state, score, answers[], created_at

## Current Status
- Login screen done (Guest + Google + Apple + state selector + language switcher)
- Setting up project structure now

## Design Style
- Clean, professional, mobile-first
- Colors: navy #0B1C3D, blue #
